to discuss this.

05:50.392 --> 05:51.727
- Stop.
- You're right.

05:52.603 --> 05:53.979
You're right. Okay.

05:53.979 --> 05:55.898
I mean, all this shit,
it always goes back to her.

05:55.898 --> 05:57.691
I mean, the old fuck
nearly got Mickey killed.

05:57.691 --> 05:59.443
I'm not even gonna call out
your ageism.

05:59.443 --> 06:00.444
F that B.

06:00.444 --> 06:01.445
Let's go.

06:01.445 --> 06:03.655
♪ ♪

06:03.655 --> 06:06.658
[fire crackling]

06:09.578 --> 06:10.871
Would you think I was crazy

06:10.871 --> 06:13.624
if I told you
I heard him again?

06:13.624 --> 06:15.459
[mysterious music]

06:15.459 --> 06:16.752
You've always taught me
it's best

06:16.752 --> 06:18.462
to leave the dead dead.

06:18.462 --> 06:21.423
So many dead in my life,
and I never hear.

06:21.423 --> 06:23.759
♪ ♪

06:23.759 --> 06:26.303
So why is Brad haunting me?

06:26.303 --> 06:28.138
♪ ♪

06:28.138 --> 06:29.473
Hmm?

06:30.808 --> 06:33.018
Maybe because of his son.

06:33.018 --> 06:37.147
You--you think he's sending me
a message from the beyond?

06:37.147 --> 06:39.358
Or maybe you're sending
yourself a message.

06:39.358 --> 06:41.443
♪ ♪

06:41.443 --> 06:42.694
To do what?

06:42.694 --> 06:44.738
To leave Mickey alone.

06:45.405 --> 06:46.990
Too late for that.

06:46.990 --> 06:48.992
[beeping]

06:50.744 --> 06:52.246
[Dylan] We have visitors.

06:53.038 --> 06:54.748
Too late for them too.

06:54.748 --> 07:00.963
♪ ♪

07:00.963 --> 07:03.966
[crow cawing]

07:12.391 --> 07:14.685
[ominous music]

07:14.685 --> 07:19.815
"Let us labor
to make the heart grow larger

07:19.815 --> 07:21.567
"as we become older,

07:21.567 --> 07:24.653
"as spreading oak gives
more shelter.

07:24.653 --> 07:29.158
Here lies E.S.,
a childhood lost for children."

07:29.158 --> 07:30.534
♪ ♪

07:30.534 --> 07:31.994
It's just so fucking creepy.

07:31.994 --> 07:32.911
Yeah.

07:32.911 --> 07:35.205
Maybe it's for a pet?

07:35.205 --> 07:37.499
[Lizzy] I was wondering
when you would come.

07:39.585 --> 07:40.961
Hey.

07:41.545 --> 07:43.589
Mickey's really hurt
because of all your bullshit.

07:43.589 --> 07:45.632
Yeah, all your fucking
mind games and shit

07:45.632 --> 07:46.884
have to stop.

07:46.884 --> 07:48.177
You need to stop.

07:49.219 --> 07:50.304
My, oh, my.

07:50.304 --> 07:51.972
The two of you swear so much.

07:51.972 --> 07:53.140
I'm sorry.

07:53.140 --> 07:54.933
Miss Fucking Bat Lady,
are you deaf?

07:54.933 --> 07:56.268
Mickey's in the hospital.

07:56.268 --> 07:57.769
- I'm aware.
- [Spoon] You're aware?

07:57.769 --> 08:00.314
Then why didn't you do
anything to help him?

08:00.314 --> 08:02.900
I am doing things to help him
right now

08:02.900 --> 08:06.695
by having the both of you here,
Miss Emma, Mr. Spindell.

08:06.695 --> 08:07.905
[Spoon]
How do you know our names?

08:07.905 --> 08:09.031
Oh, okay.

08:09.031 --> 08:11.116
Just more spooky
Bat Lady shit, right.

08:11.116 --> 08:12.242
News flash, honey.

08:12.242 --> 08:14.077
My name's Spoon,
and her name's Ema.

08:14.077 --> 08:16.079
I know all about
changing names.

08:16.079 --> 08:17.915
I chose the name Bat Lady

08:17.915 --> 08:20.417
so that the children
would be scared of me.

08:20.417 --> 08:24.546
And from what I understand,

08:24.546 --> 08:28.342
you are, Mr. Spoon.

08:28.342 --> 08:31.720
And so are you, Miss Timid Ema.

08:31.720 --> 08:32.971
♪ ♪

08:32.971 --> 08:35.307
But perhaps...

08:35.307 --> 08:39.352
perhaps you are also
the bravest of them all.

08:39.352 --> 08:43.815
♪ ♪

08:43.815 --> 08:47.194
Like, what are we supposed
to do with that, seriously?

08:47.194 --> 08:48.028
Think!

08:48.028 --> 08:51.031
[tense music]

08:51.031 --> 08:56.870
♪ ♪

08:56.870 --> 08:59.957
[screaming]

08:59.957 --> 09:00.999
[gunshot]

09:00.999 --> 09:05.212
♪ ♪

09:05.212 --> 09:06.171
Holy shit, the grave.

09:06.171 --> 09:07.506
It's for you.

09:07.506 --> 09:11.551
Yes, for a part of me,

09:11.551 --> 09:13.095
my childhood.

09:13.095 --> 09:14.554
But now...

09:14.554 --> 09:17.099
now I am Bat Lady.

09:18.183 --> 09:19.559
And now you must go.

09:19.559 --> 09:20.477
Go where?

09:20.477 --> 09:21.812
[Lizzy] Mickey began a mission,

09:21.812 --> 09:24.189
but I believe it is
your destiny to complete it.

09:24.189 --> 09:27.234
And if you don't, she will die.

09:27.234 --> 09:28.235
Ashley.

09:28.235 --> 09:30.570
- [Lizzy] Yes.
- Okay.

09:30.570 --> 09:32.864
Well, how are we supposed
to do that, though?

09:32.864 --> 09:34.491
I mean,
it's just the two of us.

09:34.491 --> 09:36.326
No, the three of you.

09:36.326 --> 09:37.369
No, we just told you.

09:37.369 --> 09:38.870
Mickey's in the hospital.

09:38.870 --> 09:40.789
Not Mickey.

09:40.789 --> 09:41.790
[person] Hi.

09:41.790 --> 09:43.250
Uh...

09:43.250 --> 09:46.378
♪ ♪

09:46.378 --> 09:47.838
Rachel Caldwell?

09:47.838 --> 09:50.007
